# Table Rows and Detail Views

When a table lists items that have a detail view (e.g. case details, entity profile, record view):

- **Do not** add a separate link/button column on the right (e.g. "View" or an arrow) as the only way to open the detail.
- **Do** make the entire table row clickable and navigate to the detail view when the row is clicked.

This improves UX (larger click target, clearer affordance) and keeps the table cleaner.

## Implementation

- Attach `onClick` (or equivalent) to the row element (`<tr>`, or the wrapper component for each row).
- Use `cursor: pointer` and optional hover styling so the row clearly looks interactive.
- Ensure keyboard accessibility (e.g. row is focusable and Enter/Space triggers navigation, or provide a visible skip link for keyboard users).
- If you need a separate control (e.g. menu or secondary action), keep it in addition to the row click; the primary navigation should still be the row click.

## Example

```tsx
// Prefer: clickable row
<tr
  onClick={() => navigate(`/cases/${row.id}`)}
  className="cursor-pointer hover:bg-muted/50"
>
  <td>{row.id}</td>
  <td>{row.name}</td>
  <td>{row.status}</td>
</tr>

// Avoid: link only in last column
<tr>
  <td>{row.id}</td>
  <td>{row.name}</td>
  <td>{row.status}</td>
  <td><Link to={`/cases/${row.id}`}>View â†’</Link></td>
</tr>
```
